  <div xmlns:v="http://rdf.data-vocabulary.org/#" typeof="v:Review">
    <div class="main review-item" id="5315730">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/5315730/" class="title-link">文学与阅读</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-5315730"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/huangxiaoya/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u4387560-20.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/huangxiaoya/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">Jasmim</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar40 main-title-rating" title="推荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2012-02-22"
      class="main-meta">2012-02-22 18:25:21</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_5315730_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                   Leonard Cohen教我们如何live with defeat，哈罗德布鲁姆和罗蒂却依然告诉我们可以在文学中找到兴奋、希望和救赎。在罗蒂看来，对宗教的信仰与对哲学的信仰已经被对文学的信仰取代。宗教信仰是人与某种非人位格之间的关系，哲学信仰是人与某种（放之四海而皆准的）真理之间的...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/5315730/#comments">(4回应)</a>
                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">27有用 / 0没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="review_5315730_full" class="hidden">
            <div id="review_5315730_full_content" class="full-content"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>





